&lt;h1 id=&#34;order-book-imbalance&#34;&gt;Order Book Imbalance&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We define the the imbalance as the difference between the bid and ask quantity quotes divided by its sum. That is,
$$
Imb_t = \frac{V^{b}_t-V^{a}_t}{V^b_t+V^{a}_t},
$$
where $V_t^{b}$ and $V_t^{a}$ denotes the volume posted at the best bid and at the best ask, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Order Book Imbalance measures whether the limit order book is buy or sell heavy. In fact, it is a good predictor of price direction. To illustrate this, in Figure 3 we plot the order imbalance for each quote at the best limits. In this figure, the blue and red dots represent buy and sell market orders, respectivelly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Divide imbalance into regimes and illustrate when trades occur.&lt;/p&gt;


